      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im looking at some preliminary census and enrollment data for the upcoming planning cycle. we're seeing some big shifts in the north and south districts. the north district is becoming much more diverse, mostly growing with Hispanic and Black families moving in. meanwhile the south district is staying pretty much the same, mostly white middle class. given the budget constraints, how should we be thinking about our curriculum investments in these two areas? like should we be looking at different types of programs for each to make sure we're being efficient?",
