      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see what u mean about engagement, but i'm more interested in the actual track placement. if the north is gonna be majority minority students, would it make sense to pivot more budgets there toward vocational training, trade certs, or life skills programs instead of, say, doubling down on advanced placement or honors-level tracks? just thinking about where the highest ROI for the students' future careers might be based on these demographics.",
